snippet.textDisplay:
I was there. Think it was the first night (they played 3). Bus out from Dublin on a pissy night to Punchestown.
It was impressive. The sound was thunderous. Problem was it was very “Kid A” centric. But it had only been released a few days earlier. So one of the fundamental elements of how we enjoy music, anticipation, was gone because nobody really knew the album yet. Maybe that was the idea though.
I remember seeing Uaneen Fitzsimons (presented a late night alternative music programme called No Disco on Irish television) queueing for Belgian waffles ahead of me. She died in a car crash a month later.
